at Canadian artist, beginning with his early attempts at defining art, to his emergence and recognition on the international art scene. This book is one of four books that are part of the Michael Snow Project. Initiated by the Art Gallery of Ontario and The Power Plant Gallery, the project also includes four exhibitions of his visual art and music.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aFine Arts. 0aSnow, Michael, 1929-xCriticism and interpretation. 0aSnow, Michael, 1929-xExhibitions. 0aSnow, Michael, 1929-xInterviews. 0aSnow, Michael, 1929-. 4aArt. 7aART / Individual Artists / Artists' Books.2bisacsh1 aDompierre, Louise, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Complete eBook-Package Pre-2010z978311127416408iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Upgrade eBook-Package pre 2010z978311127724040uhttps://doi.org/10.51644/978088920604540uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780889206045423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780889206045/original  a978-3-11-127416-4  ACUP Complete eBook-Package Pre-2010b2010  a978-3-11-127724-0  ACUP Upgrade eBook-Package pre 2010b2010  aGBV-deGruyter-alles